First, we discuss the case with cylinder length, L = 1 mm. In Fig. 4, we plot the target density distribution produced by the BIG2 code at different times. Figure. 4a is plotted at t = 75 ns, the time when the bunch has just delivered its total energy. The beam enters the target from the right side, deposits a fraction of its energy in the target material and emerges from the left side. It is seen that two shocks, Sout\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
